s.										</li>									</ol>								</li>								<li>									In <a href="2">Part 2</a>,									Keius returns to his research project investigating the connection between the nanotechnology and sapience, and creates new life de novo in the process.									<ol>										<li>											In <a href="2/1">Episode 1</a>,											Keius returns to Asira to continue his old investigation into the relation between sapient life and the nanites that gave him his powers.										</li>										<li>											In <a href="2/2">Episode 2</a>,											amidst controversy that in doing so he is breaking an ancient taboo, Keius creates entirely new life forms from his nanites, the Asiran.										</li>										<li>											In <a href="2/3">Episode 3</a>,											the Asiran are hailed as miraculous, but then turn out to pose exactly the threat that some feared they would, until Keius is barely able to reign them in.										</li>									</ol>								</li>								<li>									In <a href="3">Part 3</a>,									Keius and his lover Tatia finally consummate their relationship and have a child, right on the eve of the momentous discovery of other sapient life: humans.									<ol>										<li>											In <a href="3/1">Episode 1</a>,											Keius and Tatia gradually fall in love, but Tatia wrestles with the implications of Keius' earlier death and resurrection, and who he really is now.										</li>										<li>											In <a href="3/2">Episode 2</a>,											Keius and Tatia finally consummate their relationship, in a way that is socially unusual by Ehrban customs, conceiving their child named Lievus.										</li>										<li>											In <a href="3/3">Episode 3</a>,											an outgoing wormhole reveals prehistoric Earth to the Ehrban, and Keius becomes obsessed with studying primitive humanity, leaving Lievus to Tatia's care.										</li>									</ol>								</li>							</ol>						</li>					</ol>				</section><? require $_SERVER['DOCUMENT_ROOT'] . "/includes/footer-global.php" ?>